description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COME AND JOIN US on our 32 bedded Orthopaedic elective and trauma ward.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are a proactive patient and staff centered team who strive for excellence and to make a difference to our patients and provide staff with job satisfaction.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A friendly, supportive multi-professional team spirit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Orthopaedic specialist nurses, occupational therapists and physiotherapists are integral to the team and are ward based.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We value everyone’s contribution to making positive changes for patients and staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A new staffing model was implemented in April 2019 to support more time for nursing staff to be at the bedside&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 RGN and 1 HCA per 7-8 patients.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generic Support Worker to release time to care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An induction programme tailored to support your individual professional development and career aspirations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shadowing opportunities for your induction period with Acute Pain Service, Specialist Nurses and theatres&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fantastic job satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated ward meeting space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A light, bright and airy ward with a beautiful outside space for patients and staff to enjoy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We welcome full time, part time and flexible applications&lt;/strong&gt; from those of you with a genuine interest in Orthopaedic Nursing. A caring, compassionate, patient-centred approach is the most important qualities for us and we will welcome and support you to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week: 37.5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift patterns:shifts will be either early (7:00-15:00), late (13:00-20:00), long day (7:00-20:00) or night shifts (19:30-7:30)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For details about the role and ward/informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Selena King&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Sister Ward 10&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;01625 663354&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For queries regarding the application and or interview process, please contact the Recruitment Team either via email, ecn-tr.recruitment@nhs.net or telephone, 01625 656510&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We would like to inform you that if your application is successful, your interview will be held via SKYPE.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
